parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion or deformation of the fuel tank can cause it to detach from its mounts, leading to a loss of fuel tank security, potential fuel leaks, and increased risk of accidents or fires.
symptoms: The fuel tank is expanding or deforming
causing it to loosen from its mounts
rub against the handlebars or fork
and exhibit cracks or bubbles in the paint.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas Tank Distortion and Failure Due to Ethanol in Fuel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The distortion of the gas tank can cause it to fall off its mounts, interfering with the steering of the motorcycle, and potentially leading to fuel leakage onto the engine and exhaust system, which can result in a fire hazard.
symptoms: The gas tank distorts from its original shape
the tank falls off its mounts
the tank interferes with the steering of the motorcycle
the tank wears on the frame
fuel leakage onto the engine and exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation and collapse of the gas tank can cause the tank to become loose and potentially lead to fuel leaks, which can be a fire hazard, and also affect the overall performance and safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: The gas tank is no longer securely held in place
the tank can be easily lifted up
the tank has developed "dimples" or large dents on the surface
